"""
There are 10 touch points in a complete roundtrip, ignoring expception handling

1) Client
   1.1) Extensions
   1.2) Serializer
   1.3) Handler
2) Service
   2.1) Handler
   2.2) Serializer
   2.3) Extensions
   2.4) Binding engine
   2.5) Service-side functions

A single call looks like this:

CLIENT       === CLIENT OPERATION CALL ===
|          | - Extensions manipulate input dict
|          | - Serialize input dict -> string
|          | - Handler builds URI for operation, pushes string as body
V          V === INTERNET MAGIC HERE ===
SERVICE    | - Server receives body at operation-specific URI
|          | - Serializer for wire format deserializes body to input dict
|          | - Extensions manipulate input dict
|          | - Binding engine maps input dict to function
V          V === SERVICE FUNCTION INVOCATION ===
|          | - Binding engine maps result to output dict
|          | - Extensions manipulate output dict
|          | - Serializer for wire format serializes output dict to body
V          V === INTERNET MAGIC HERE ===
CLIENT     | - Handler gets response for operation
|          | - Serializer for wire format deserializes body to output dict
|          | - Extensions manipulate output dict
V            === CLIENT OEPRATION RETURNS ===
"""
